{"questionId":"22572344","questionHtml":"<p>Explain why the probability that the first boost occurs on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>th</mi></msup></math> action is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>there will be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math> actions not boosted, followed by one boosted action&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>The <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>th</mi></msup></math> action is boosted and all previous actions are not boosted&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mrow><munder><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mo>⏟</mo></munder><mo>×</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>times</mi></mrow></munder></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> For the <strong>OR</strong> method, the order of the operations must be clear (accept also a tree diagram etc.).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22572344","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ1.1bi","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Explain why the probability that the first boost occurs on the xth action is p1-px-1.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}